e]] | {{Australian party style|Liberal}}|&nbsp; | rowspan=3 | Liberal | rowspan=3 | [[John Howard|Howard]] | Minister for Industry, Science and Tourism | align=center |11 March 1996 | align=center |21 October 1998 | align=right |{{age in years and days|1996|3|11|1998|10|21}} |- | align=center| 21 | [[Nick Minchin]] | {{Australian party style|Liberal}}|&nbsp; | Minister for Industry, Science and Resources | align=center |21 October 1998 | align=center |26 November 2001 | align=right |{{age in years and days|1998|10|21|2001|11|26}} |- | align=center| 22 | [[Ian Macfarlane (politician)|Ian Macfarlane]] | {{Australian party style|Liberal}}|&nbsp; | Minister for Industry, Tourism and Resources | align=center |26 November 2001 | align=center |3 December 2007 | align=right |{{age in years and days|2001|11|26|2007|12|3}} |- | rowspan=2 align=center | 23 | rowspan=2 | [[Kim Carr]] | {{Australian party style|Labor}}| | rowspan=4 | Labor | [[Kevin Rudd|Rudd]] | rowspan=2 | Minister for Innovation, Industry, Science and Research | align=center | 3 December 2007 | align=center | 24 June 2010 | rowspan=2 align=right | {{age in years and days|2007|12|3|2011|12|14}} |- | {{Australian party style|Labor}}| | rowspan=2 | [[Julia Gillard|Gillard]] | align=center | 24 June 2010 | align=center | 14 December 2011 |- | align=center | 24 | [[Greg Combet]] | {{Australian party style|Labor}}| | Minister for Industry and Innovation | align=center | 14 December 2011 | align=center | 26 June 2013 | align=right | {{age in years and days|2011|12|14|2013|6|26}} |- | align=center | ''(23)'' | [[Kim Carr]] | {{Australian party style|Labor}}| | Rudd | Minister for Innovation, Industry, Science and Research | align=center | 26 June 2013 | align=center | 18 September 2013 | align=right | {{age in days|2013|6|26|2013|11|18}} days |- | rowspan=3 align=center| ''(22)'' | rowspan=3 | [[Ian Macfarlane (politician)|Ian Macfarlane]] | {{Australian party style|LNP}}|&nbsp; | rowspan=3 | [[Liberal National Party